@NODE 0. "Getting Started"
                           Getting Started.

    * Don't have up-to-date ClassAct Classes? 
    * Connect to www.finale-dev.com and look in the Downloads area
    * for free updates.                       

	Double click on the install icon to install WebFTP.
	
	Once it is installed:

	From the WorkBench: double click on the WebFTP icon.
	From a shell: type "WebFTP" and hit return.

	Once the Window has opened, click on the chooser button to select
	a pre configured site or the config program will open allowing you
	to enter your remote and local @{"configuration." Link 1.}

	If your home directory hasn't been setup for you by your admin, get
	in contact with them and ask for it to be done.
	
	Most remote servers use "public_html" as the directory for your
	html, if this is not the case, contact your admin and ask what it
	is. Once you know what directory to use, enter it into the config
	for that site.
	
	If you want to setup your own directory, click on the MkDir button
	and enter the name of the directory you want to create. Don't
	forget to change your remote @{"configuration." Link 1.}
@ENDNODE

@NODE 1. "Configuration"
                         Configuring WebFTP.

	Use the pulldown menu to select WebFTP, or run the WebFTPCfg
	program supplied.

	To add a new site:
		o Click on the "Add" button.
		o Enter site name.
		o Enter site address.
		o Enter username and password.
		o Enter the remote directory of your html files.
		o Enter the local root directory of your html files.
		o Select if you want to delete the obsolete remote files.
		o Select if you want a screen beep on upload completion.
		o Click on the "Save" button to save the changes.

	To modify an old site:
		o Click on the site name in the site list.
		o Change site name.
		o Change site address.
		o Change username and password.
		o Change the remote directory of your html files.
		o Change the local root directory of your html files.
		o Click on the "Save" button to save the changes.

	Two new options have been added to the "Prefs" pull down menu:
		o Refresh Remote.
		o Refresh Local.

	If you have large local and remote directories, you might want to
	un-select these two options.
	
	If your Amiga is on a LAN, then enter the LAN gateway proxy IP
	in the "LAN Proxy" string gadget. This MUST be an IP number.
	If you dont use a LAN, then dont put anything in this.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "Usage"
                         Updating your site.

	When you have connected to your remote host, you will see (left
	side) all the remote files, if any, and on the right is your local
	html directory.

	For ease of use, WebFTP uses the assign "LocalHTML:" for the root
	directory of all your local web pages. (Does NOT need to be set)

	Now all you have to do is click on the "Compare" button and wait
	for WebFTP to compare all your local files to your remote files.

	If you have "delete unused remote files" selected, WebFTP will mark
	all unused files on your remote host with a Trashcan, and mark
	other files remote/local, with differant icons.

	Once this has finished, all you have to do is click on the
	"Update" button, and WebFTP will start deleting (if selected) the
	unused remote files, then it will start uploading the new/updated
	files from your harddrive to the remote site.

	WebFTP will not delete any files that start with a dot, ie.
	".bash_history".

	To Auto Ignore any remote files, enter the file extention for that
	type of file to the WebFTP.ignore file.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 3. "File Menu's"
                             File Menu's

@{" File Menu's - Remote" Link 4.}
@{" File Menu's - Local" Link 5.}
@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "File Menu's - Remote"
                    Using the remote file menu's.

	There are 7 (seven) menu items for use with the remote files.

   	o view   - View the remote file.
   	o Delete - Delete the remote file.
   	o Rename - Rename the remote file.
   	o chmod  - Change the mode on the remote file.
   	o touch  - Set the date on the remote file.
   	o Ignore - Set the ignore icon for the remote file.
   	o Info   - Display info for selected file.

	To access this menu, double click on a remote filename.

	Chmod can only be used if your remote host allows the use
	of the "SITE <cmd>" command. If in doubt, ask your system admin.
	
	View uses multiview to display the file.
	WARNING: Delete gives no warnings.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 5. "File Menu's - Local"
                     Using the local file menu's.

	There are 4 (four) menu items for the local files.

   	o View   - View the local file.
   	o Ignore - Set the ignore icon for the local file.
   	o Delete - Delete the local file.
   	o Info   - Display info for selected file.

	To access the menu for the local files, double click on a local
	filename.
	
	View uses multiview to display the file.
	WARNING: Delete gives no warnings.
@ENDNODE

@NODE 6. "Other"
                                Other.

	For those of you that like to see everything that goes on, WebFTP
	has a "Debug" option (select it in the pulldown menu). This will
	open a listbrowser at the bottom of the window and will log all
	commands that are received from the remote host. This debug
	listbrowser will also log any errors.

@ENDNODE

